{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0615b57d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s3705"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3705"},"text":"§ 3705.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reporting requirement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The President shall submit to the Congress, not later than 1 year after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-18"},"text":"May 18, 2000","children":[],"tail":", and annually thereafter through 2008, a comprehensive report on the trade and investment policy of the United States for sub-Saharan Africa, and on the implementation of this chapter and the amendments made by this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0615b57e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/200/tI/s106"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–200, title I, § 106","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-18"},"text":"May 18, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/256"},"text":"114 Stat. 256","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id0615b57f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id0615b580-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id0615b581-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this title”, meaning title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/200"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–200","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-18"},"text":"May 18, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/252"},"text":"114 Stat. 252","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this chapter and sections 2466a and 2466b of this title and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2463"},"text":"section 2463 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and former section 2193 and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2293"},"text":"section 2293 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s3701"},"text":"section 3701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id0615b582-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id0615b583-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reports on Implementation and Potential Trade Agreements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/tI/s110"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–27, title I, § 110","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/370"},"text":"129 Stat. 370","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/114/27/tI/s110"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Implementation Report.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 1 year after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 2015","children":[],"tail":"], and biennially thereafter, the President shall submit to Congress a report on the trade and investment relationship between the United States and sub-Saharan African countries and on the implementation of this title [see Short Title of 2015 Amendment note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s3701"},"text":"section 3701 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] and the amendments made by this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Matters to be included","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The report required by paragraph (1) shall include the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A description of the status of trade and investment between the United States and sub-Saharan Africa, including information on leading exports to the United States from sub-Saharan African countries.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any changes in eligibility of sub-Saharan African countries during the period covered by the report.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A detailed analysis of whether each such beneficiary sub-Saharan African country is continuing to meet the eligibility requirements set forth in section 104 of the African Growth and Opportunity Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s3703"},"text":"19 U.S.C. 3703","children":[],"tail":"] and the eligibility criteria set forth in section 502 of the Trade Act of 1974 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2462"},"text":"19 U.S.C. 2462","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"“(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A description of the status of regional integration efforts in sub-Saharan Africa.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"“(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A summary of United States trade capacity building efforts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"“(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any other initiatives related to enhancing the trade and investment relationship between the United States and sub-Saharan African countries.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Potential Trade Agreements Report","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 1 year after the date of the enactment of this Act, and every 5 years thereafter, the United States Trade Representative shall submit to Congress a report that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" identifies sub-Saharan African countries that have a [sic] expressed an interest in entering into a free trade agreement with the United States;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" evaluates the viability and progress of such sub-Saharan African countries and other sub-Saharan African countries toward entering into a free trade agreement with the United States; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" describes a plan for negotiating and concluding such agreements, which includes the elements described in subparagraphs (A) through (E) of section 116(b)(2) of the African Growth and Opportunity Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s3723/b/2"},"text":"19 U.S.C. 3723(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Termination","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The reporting requirements of this section shall cease to have any force or effect after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2025","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[Functions of President under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/s110/a"},"text":"section 110(a) of Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", set out above, assigned to United States Trade Representative, in consultation with Secretary of State, see Ex. Ord. No. 13720, § 1(d), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-26"},"text":"Feb. 26, 2016","children":[],"tail":", 81 F.R. 11089, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s2466a"},"text":"section 2466a of this title","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[For definitions of “beneficiary sub-Saharan African country” and “sub-Saharan African country” as used in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/s110"},"text":"section 110 of Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", set out above, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/27/s112"},"text":"section 112 of Pub. L. 114–27","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s3701"},"text":"section 3701 of this title","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id0615b584-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"delegationOfFunctions","id":"id0615b585-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Delegation of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of President under this section delegated to United States Trade Representative by section 1(b) of Ex. Ord. No. 13346, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-07-08"},"text":"July 8, 2004","children":[],"tail":", 69 F.R. 41905, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t3/s301"},"text":"section 301 of Title 3","children":[],"tail":", The President."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
